<p><span class="emph2">Welcome to NINES</span> &mdash; a networked interface for nineteenth-century electronic scholarship.  This site uses <a href="http://www.patacriticism.org/collex" target="_blank">Collex</a>, a collections and exhibits tool for the remixable web, to aggregate peer-reviewed online scholarship and allow you to collect, annotate, and share it with students and colleagues.  The NINES site is both a proof of concept and a work in progress &mdash; so check back often for updates to the interface and scholarly content.

<p>More information about <%= link_to "digital objects", { :action => "resources" }, :popup => ['window_resources', 'height=400,width=300,top=50,left=50'] %> and <%= link_to "projects included", { :action => "sites" }, :popup => ['window_sites', 'height=400,width=300,top=50,left=50'] %> in NINES is available, as are detailed technical descriptions of the NINES <a href="http://www.nines.org/about/9swhitepaper.pdf" target="_blank">federation</a> and <a href="http://www.nines.org/about/Nowviskie-Collex.pdf" target="_blank">Collex</a>.
